# Research Report: Agent Color Definition & TUI Parsing Pipeline

**Task:** 41 | **Subtask:** 92
**Worker:** d-t2-w1 (pane 2.1)
**Date:** 2026-04-10

## Summary

Agent colors are defined as hex strings (e.g. `"#FF6B35"`) in YAML frontmatter of `.md` files in `agents/`. The Go TUI parses these with a lightweight custom frontmatter parser (not a full YAML library), stores the raw hex string in both an SQLite database and in-memory structs, and passes it directly to `lipgloss.Color()` for terminal rendering. **There is no validation, transformation, or normalization of the color value anywhere in the pipeline.**

## Findings

### 1. Color Definition in Agent .md Files

**Format:** Hex color strings with `#` prefix, quoted in YAML frontmatter.

| Agent | Color | File |
|-------|-------|------|
| doey-taskmaster | `#FF6B35` | `agents/doey-taskmaster.md:4` |
| doey-subtaskmaster | `#2ECC71` | `agents/doey-subtaskmaster.md:4` |
| doey-worker | `#3498DB` | `agents/doey-worker.md:4` |
| doey-critic | `#E74C3C` | `agents/doey-critic.md:4` |
| seo-manager | `#27AE60` | `agents/seo-manager.md:4` |
| visual-manager | `#9B59B6` | `agents/visual-manager.md:4` |

All inspected agents use **uppercase 6-digit hex** with `#` prefix, quoted with double quotes. The YAML field is simply `color: "#RRGGBB"`.

### 2. Frontmatter Parsing (Go)

Two independent parsers exist:

**A. Runtime reader parser** (`tui/internal/runtime/reader.go:1193-1230`):
- Function: `parseFrontmatter(path string) map[string]string`
- Reads lines between `---` delimiters
- Splits on first `:`, trims whitespace
- Strips surrounding `"` or `'` quotes
- Returns raw `map[string]string` — no type coercion, no validation
- Color value is stored as-is (e.g. `"#FF6B35"` after quote stripping)

**B. Store migration parser** (`tui/internal/store/migrate.go:658-705`):
- Function: `parseFrontmatter(path string) (map[string]string, string, error)`
- Also returns the body text after frontmatter
- Same key:value split-on-first-colon approach
- Strips `"` and `'` quotes via `strings.Trim(v, "\"'")`
- Used during DB migration to seed agent records

### 3. Data Model / Structs

**Runtime AgentDef** (`tui/internal/runtime/types.go:237-246`):
```go
type AgentDef struct {
    Name        string   `json:"name"`
    Description string   `json:"description"`
    Model       string   `json:"model"`
    Color       string   `json:"color"`        // raw hex string
    Memory      string   `json:"memory"`
    Domain      string   `json:"domain"`
    FilePath    string   `json:"filepath"`
    UsedByTeams []string `json:"used_by_teams"`
}
```

**Store Agent** (`tui/internal/store/agents.go:4-11`):
```go
type Agent struct {
    Name        string `json:"name"`
    DisplayName string `json:"display_name"`
    Model       string `json:"model,omitempty"`
    Description string `json:"description,omitempty"`
    Color       string `json:"color,omitempty"`     // raw hex string
    FilePath    string `json:"file_path,omitempty"`
}
```

### 4. Storage Layer (SQLite)

**Schema** (`tui/internal/store/schema.go:104-110`):
```sql
CREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS agents (
    name TEXT PRIMARY KEY,
    display_name TEXT,
    model TEXT,
    description TEXT,
    color TEXT NOT NULL DEFAULT '',
    file_path TEXT
);
```

The `color` column was added via migration (`schema.go:186`):
```sql
ALTER TABLE agents ADD COLUMN color TEXT DEFAULT ''
```

**Agent CRUD** (`tui/internal/store/agents.go`):
- `UpsertAgent()` — INSERT OR REPLACE, stores color as raw text
- `GetAgent()` — SELECT, reads color back as raw text
- `ListAgents()` — SELECT all, color as raw text
- No color validation at the store level

### 5. Data Flow: .md File -> TUI Rendering

```
agents/*.md  (color: "#FF6B35")
     |
     v
parseFrontmatter()  [reader.go:1193 OR migrate.go:658]
     |  strips quotes -> "#FF6B35"
     v
readAgentDefs()  [reader.go:976] ─── creates AgentDef{Color: "#FF6B35"}
     |                                      OR
migrateOneAgent()  [migrate.go:429] ── INSERT INTO agents ... color="#FF6B35"
     |                                      |
     v                                      v
Snapshot.AgentDefs               storeReader.readAgents() [store_reader.go:248]
     |                                      |
     ├── tried first (store) ───────────────┘
     |
     v
model.AgentsModel.View()  [agents.go:275+]
     |
     v
lipgloss.Color(agent.Color)  [agents.go:391, 501, 556, 618]
     |
     v
Terminal renders the color (ANSI true-color escape)
```

**Snapshot loading priority** (`reader.go:173-179`):
1. Try store: `r.sr.readAgents()` — converts `store.Agent` -> `runtime.AgentDef`
2. Fallback to files: `r.readAgentDefs(projectDir)` — parses `.md` frontmatter directly

### 6. Color Rendering in TUI

The color string is passed directly to `lipgloss.Color()` in four places in `agents.go`:

- **Line 391:** Left panel agent list — colored `◆` dot next to agent name
- **Line 501:** Detail panel — colored `◆` dot next to "Color" label + dim hex text
- **Line 556:** `maxRightScroll()` calculation — replicates title dot styling
- **Line 618:** Right panel header — colored `◆` dot before agent name title

`lipgloss.Color()` accepts: hex (`#RRGGBB`, `#RGB`), ANSI 256 colors (`0`-`255`), or named CSS colors. There is no Doey-side validation — invalid strings would silently render as default terminal color.

### 7. Shell-side Usage

The settings panel (`shell/settings-panel.sh:648-696`) also reads agent colors:
- Parses frontmatter with `_parse_agent_all()`
- Displays color value as plain text in the detail view (line 688, 743)
- Does NOT render the color visually in shell — just prints the hex string

